CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F351A1784917111
OL,3,CIsland electricity bills to be
OL,4,Csubsidised for the rest of the year
OL,6,FAlderney Electricity now says the need
OL,7,Ffor government intervention highlights
OL,8,Fjust why renewable sources are vital
OL,9,Ffor the island's future energy supply.
OL,11,FThe temporary subsidy means that
OL,12,Faverage household bills will reduce by
OL,13,Faround #30 starting from 1 July 2026.
OL,15,FThe island imports around 4-5 million
OL,16,Flitres of fuel per year and remains
OL,17,Falmost entirely reliant on fuel to
OL,18,Fgenerate electricity.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/5
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
